ğŸ§© Clarification on Filling Load Devices, DC Plant Panel, and DC Panel Breaker Sheets

Hi Team,

Based on your queries regarding Load Devices, DC Plant Panel, and DC Plant Panel Breakers, hereâ€™s a clarification to help you fill the template sheets correctly.

âš¡ 1. Load Devices

The Load Devices sheet represents the interconnection components between the line side and load side in the power path.

These devices act as the link between sources like Transformers / Generators / ATS Switchboards and the bus or extension panels that distribute power further down the chain.

In simpler terms:

From Transformers â†’ Bus / Extension â†’ Load Device connects them.

From Generators â†’ Bus / Extension â†’ Load Device connects them.

From Bus â†’ Downstream Switchboards or Extensions, the Load Device defines the connection path.


When filling the sheet:

Enter the source asset name (e.g., Transformer or Generator) in the â€œLine Sideâ€ column.

Enter the target asset (e.g., Bus or Extension) in the â€œLoad Sideâ€ column.

Mention the Load Device name / tag in the â€œDevice Nameâ€ column.

Provide comments if the device is physically located between transformer and bus, or generator and bus.



Weâ€™ll share a sample filled sheet for reference to ensure consistent naming and mapping.


---

ğŸ”‹ 2. DC Plant Panel

The DC Plant Panel represents the distribution panel that receives DC power from the DC Plant and supplies it to downstream equipment such as BDFBs or Rectifiers.

Each Plant may have one or more Panels; this mapping ensures the DC power chain continuity.


When filling:

Map each Plant Panel under its corresponding DC Plant.

Use consistent naming (e.g., Plant1-PanelA).



---

âš™ï¸ 3. DC Plant Panel Breakers

These are the individual breaker circuits within the DC Plant Panel.

They define the outgoing connections from the Plant Panel to BDFBs or other downstream devices.

Each breaker record should specify:

The Parent Panel Name (from the DC Plant Panel sheet)

The Breaker Name or ID

The Load Device / BDFB / Equipment that this breaker feeds.



The correct structure to maintain the DC power chain in DC Track will be:
ğŸ‘‰ Plant / Plant Panel : Plant Panel Breakers â†’ BDFB â†’ BDFB Panel : BDFB Panel Breakers â†’ Cabinet / Device


